Stadium Ticket RESTful API for POSIX Operating Systems

This project has been tested with the following versions of Python:
2.6.8 and 2.7.2.

This project has been tested on the following platforms:  Debian 10,
Ubuntu 18.04 LTS, Ubuntu 19.04, openSUSE Tumbleweed 20190419, Fedora 29,
macOS 10.14, FreeBSD 11.2, FreeBSD 12.0, OpenIndiana Hipster 2018.10 and
CentOS 7 1810.

NOTE: Local installation is only supported on Ubuntu and openSUSE.

1.  To install dependencies (may require sudo):

    scripts/install-dependencies.sh

2.  To initialize the database schema:

    scripts/run.sh python3 -m app init-db (or "make init-db")

3.  To run the unit tests using pytest:

    scripts/run.sh pytest (or "make pytest")

4.  To run the app in debugging mode:

    scripts/run.sh flask run (or "make debug")

5.  To test the app:

    scripts/app-test.sh (or "make client")

6.  To stress test the app:

    scripts/load-test.sh (or "make stress")

7.  To build and run a Docker container (may require sudo):

    scripts/run.sh docker-compose up --build (or "make build")

8. To install the app as a service (may require sudo):

   scripts/install-service.sh (or "make install")

9. To uninstall the app as a service (may require sudo):

   scripts/uninstall-service.sh (or "make uninstall")
